venues.name: Neal S Blaisdell Arena

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Address: 777 Ward Avenue, Honolulu, Hawaii 96814 Phone: (808) 768-5252 (events information recording) For Advance Ticket Sales Main Box Office (Arena) Hours: ** Monday - Saturday, 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM **Closed on Sunday and all Holidays unless there is a scheduled event for that day and only that event will be sold For Day of Event Ticket Sales Main Box Office (Arena) Hours: Closed on Sundays, and all Holidays unless there is a scheduled event for that day. Monday to Friday, 10:00 AM 2 (two) hours prior to the start of the event. Saturday, Sunday & Holidays, 9:00 AM 2 (two) hours prior to the start of the event
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Visa, MC, AMX, DSC & Cash. No Checks. ATM located nearby.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call may be picked up at any window at any time that the box office is open. Customers do not need to wait until the night of the show.

venues.parkingDetail: Cost: Event Parking: Before 5PM: $6.00 After 5PM: $7.00 In/Out Pass: $8.00 (In/Out Good Only For Day of Purchase @ Parking Booth) Non-Event Parking (Daily): $6.00 VIP Parking available for select events - $23.00 Elite VIP Parking: VIP Parking is open for ticket holders only, subject to availability Select Blaisdell Arena events – enter off of Ward Ave., South (Makai) of Box Office Select Concert Hall and Exhibition events – enter off of Ward Ave. between Exhibition Hall and Concert Hall Note: No left turn permitted on Ward Ave. into driveways Hours of Operation – 1 hour prior to event until end of event time VIP Parking Customer Service: For Elite VIP Parking purchased through Ticketmaster call customer service at 1-877-750-4400 Box Office Parking: Box Office Parking is open for ticket buyers only. Parking for the patrons of the Box Office is free. If Box Office Parking is full, ticket buyers may enter through the King Street Gate. The ticket buyers will be re-funded the parking fee after they validate their ticket at the Box Office. King Street Entrance: This is the main entrance to the Blaisdell Parking Lot. The gate opens at 5:30 a.m., Monday through Saturday. The gate closes at 6:00 p.m. on all evenings with no event scheduled. The gate closes 45 minutes after the last event is completed. On Sundays and Holidays, gate operation is determined by events. Kapiolani Entrance: This entrance is closed when there are no events scheduled. Only cardholders can access this gate when it is unattended. Signs are posted to direct non-card holders to the King Street entrance. This gate will also be open two hours prior to the opening of all major events scheduled in the central areas and will remain open until the completion of the last event. Hours of Operation: Non-Event Days (Mon-Fri) 5:30am - 5:00pm Event Days (Mon-Fri) 5:30am - end of night (event night) Event Days (Weekends & Holidays) 2 Hours prior to start of event - end of night Parking Booths close 45 minutes prior to end of last event.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is available in the lower level of Blaisdell Arena. No elevators for upper level or loge seating.

generalInfo.childRule: All minors should be in the control of an accompanying adult.

events.info: 56 Years Of Funk & SoulTower of PowerFor 56 years, Tower of Power has delivered the best in funk and soul music. East Bay Grease defined their sound and landed them with Warner Brothers. Bump City, their 1972 debut for the label, was a hit on both the Billboard 200 and the RYoure Still A Young Man and Down to The Nightclub. The 70s were a boom period with radio classics like So Very Hard to Go and What Is Hip?, and the band continued to tour and record over the years. Castillo says their love of the stage is the same today as it was back in 1968. events.name: Haley Reinhart
events.info: Haley ReinhartA timeless voice outlasts eras. It feels just as at home in the sixties as it does in the TikTokage. It also resounds louder as time goes on. Haley Reinhart brandishes such a voice. The expansivescope of her range comes into full focus on her 4th album, Lo-Fi Soul. The double platinum-certified Chicago-born/Los Angeles-based singer and songwriter exudes anempowering level of charisma and confidence earned by a quiet, decade-long grind. In 2024, Haley has taken her career to another level. After spending the first half of the yearwriting and recording a new album, Haley will embark on her headline tour, which will run fromMay to November 2024. events.name: Takuya Kuroda with The Dae Han Experience
events.info: Takuya Kuroda with The Dae Han ExperienceWhether moving from Japan to the U.S. or navigating between the influences of jazz, soul, hip-hop, Afrobeat and electronica, trumpeter/composer Takuya Kuroda has never followed a straight path. On his fifth studio album and Concord Records debut, the aptly named Zigzagger, Kuroda darts between those wide-ranging interests with a funky swagger and an intensely swinging vigor. The deeply infectious album, finds the trumpeter snaking his way around the opposing poles of acoustic and electric, bristling grooves and blissed-out vibes, punchy brass and fluid synths, carving his own distinctive sonic path along the way.Life is sometimes not that easy, sometimes not so difficult, and it should never go straight, Kuroda says. Its always zigzagging. So I put I my soul and spirit into that word.Tickets $25-$35__________________________________________CLUB POLICIESSeating is Communal & First Come, First Served$10 Food or Beverage Minimum Per Person Full Bar & Full Dinner Menu AvailableNo refunds or exchange. events.name: Air Supply
events.info: KSSK PresentsAir SupplyGraham Russell and Russell Hitchcock met on May 12, 1975, the first day of rehearsals for Jesus Christ Superstar in Sydney, Australia; they became instant friends with their common love for The Beatles and, of course, singing. Seven top-five singles later, Air Supply equaled The Beatles run of consecutive top five singles. Their albums have sold in excess of 20 million copies, Lost in Love was named Song of the Year in 1980 and in 2013, the duo was inducted into the Australian Recording Industry Associations Hall of Fame.Tickets $95-$165__________________________________________CLUB POLICIESSeating is Communal & First Come, First Served$10 Food or Beverage Minimum Per Person Full Bar & Full Dinner Menu AvailableNo refunds or exchange.
